main event: Disc-shaped, pinkish-orange object observed over Keflavik Airport by four officers of 932 ACW Sq.
interesting points: The object traveled at high speed, 2-3,000 feet, and hovered momentarily over the airport.
Two small lights, about 1/2 degree apart and 10-15 degrees above the horizon, were observed traveling at a rate of 4-8 degrees per minute.
One of the lights seemed to increase in intensity for a second or two, then suddenly went out.
The objects were not blinking lights, indicating they were not aircraft.
Radar at the Keflavik installation did not pick up any targets corresponding to the objects.
sighted object: disc-shaped, pinkish-orange object; two small lights
witnesses: four officers of 932 ACW Sq.; tower operator
